speech.p: Is the Secretary of State aware that not all of us who are in the categories that qualify for the flu jab have responded? I suppose that I qualify. I am having a tumour removed and I am having a heart bypass. I have a lot to thank the national health service for, and I rise to support it again. I have heard the figures. Will my right hon. Friend confirm that in the last year of the Tory Government there were 6 million flu jabs, yet this year there have been a record 14 million flu jabs? When I have mine next week, if I go—I found out this morning that it will be available—it will be 14 million and one, at least. Can there be a more sickening sight than Tory MPs who voted against—
